  <p>Your pharmacy choice directly affects your Medicare drug costs. Part D plans and Medicare Advantage plans with drug coverage offer lower pricing at "preferred" pharmacies — and the preferred pharmacy varies by plan.</p>

  <h2>Pharmacies in Vernal and the Uintah Basin</h2>
  <p><strong>Smith's Pharmacy</strong> — 1080 W Hwy 40, Vernal. Full-service pharmacy inside Smith's grocery. Many Part D plans list Smith's as a preferred or standard network pharmacy. This is also where Vernal Medicare operates. <strong>Walgreens</strong> — Vernal location. National chain with extensive Part D plan participation. <strong>Other options:</strong> Independent pharmacies, Walmart (Roosevelt), and mail-order pharmacy services.</p>

  <h2>Preferred vs Standard Pharmacy Pricing</h2>
  <p>Part D plans have two pharmacy tiers: preferred and standard. The same drug on the same plan can cost significantly less at a preferred pharmacy. For example, a generic drug might cost $1 at a preferred pharmacy and $10 at a standard one. We always check preferred pharmacy designations when comparing plans for Vernal residents.</p>

  <h2>Mail-Order Pharmacy Options</h2>
  <p>For maintenance medications (drugs you take regularly), mail-order pharmacies often provide 90-day supplies at lower per-unit costs. Most Part D plans include mail-order options. This can be especially convenient for Vernal residents who may not want to make frequent pharmacy trips.</p>

  <h2>How We Compare Pharmacy Costs</h2>
  <p>When we review your Part D options, we check each plan's pricing at your preferred pharmacy, identify which pharmacy is preferred for the plans that cover your drugs best, calculate total annual cost including premiums, copays, and deductible, and verify that all your medications are on the plan's formulary.</p>

